1) Visualize alignment

Load and process multi-fasta file from Bahia

Load package msa: multiple sequence alignment

library("msa")

Load multi-fasta from Bahia. This file contains pangolin and bat sequences. This file is not aligned and we have another multi-fasta file called extremo_sul_muscle.fasta, that was aligned using MUSCLE.

fastas_sars_cov2_ba <- readDNAStringSet(file="../dados/extremo_sul_combined/extremo_sul.fasta")

Subset from positions 1bp to 350bp

Information about subsetting strings was gained from Chapter 4: Manipulating Sequences with Biostrings, found in Gatto (2023).

seq_1_to_350 <- subseq(fastas_sars_cov2_ba, start = 1, end = 350)

Print sequence

print(seq_1_to_350)
## DNAStringSet object of length 10:
##      width seq                                              names               
##  [1]   350 ATTAAAGGTTTATACCTTCCCAG...CAGGTTCGCGACGTGCTCGTAC NC_045512.2 Wuhan...
##  [2]   350 ACTCTCGATCTCTTGTAGATCTG...CGTGGAGGAGGCTTTATCAGAG hCoV-19/bat/Yunna...
##  [3]   350 ACCAACCAACTTTCGATCTCTTG...GGAGACTCCGTGGAGGAGGTCT hCoV-19/Brazil/MG...
##  [4]   350 ACCAACTTTCGATCTCTTGTAGA...ACTCCGTGGAGGAGGTCTTATC hCoV-19/Brazil/BA...
##  [5]   350 ACCAACTTTCGATCTCTTGTAGA...ACTCCGTGGAGGAGGTCTTATC hCoV-19/Brazil/BA...
##  [6]   350 TTAAAATCTGTGTGGCTGTCACT...AGGATGGCACTTGTGGCTTAGT hCoV-19/pangolin/...
##  [7]   350 CTTTCGATCTCTTGTAGATCTGT...GTGGAGGAGGTCTTATCAGAGG hCoV-19/Brazil/BA...
##  [8]   350 CAACTTTCGATCTCTTGTAGATC...TCCGTGGAGGAGGTCTTATCAG hCoV-19/Brazil/BA...

## [10]   350 TTCCCAGGTAACAAACCAACCAA...TCGTACGTGGCTTTGGAGACTC hCoV-19/Brazil/ES...

Align sequences

start_time <- Sys.time()
alignment_ba_1_to_350 <- msa(seq_1_to_350)
## use default substitution matrix
end_time <- Sys.time()
end_time - start_time
## Time difference of 0.14995 secs
alignment_ba_1_to_350

Export and import msa object

saveRDS(multiple_fasta_almt_ba, file = "../dados/multiple_fasta_almt_ba.rds")
multiple_fasta_almt_ba_read <- readRDS("../dados/multiple_fasta_almt_ba.rds")

Print alignment

msaPrettyPrint(alignment_ba_1_to_350, output="pdf", showNames="none",
               showLogo="none", askForOverwrite=FALSE, verbose=FALSE)

Print Logo

msaPrettyPrint(alignment_ba_1_to_350, output="pdf",## y=c(164, 213),
               #subset=c(1:6), 
               showNames="none", showLogo="top",
               logoColors="rasmol", shadingMode="similar",
               showLegend=FALSE, askForOverwrite=FALSE)

2) Distance Matrix and Phylogenetic Tree of Partial Sequence

This is necessary so function dist.ml can take the DNA.bin object and process the Distance Matrix. Function dist.ml() is from package phangorn

library("phangorn")
## Warning: package 'phangorn' was built under R version 4.1.2
## Loading required package: ape
## Warning: package 'ape' was built under R version 4.1.2
## 
## Attaching package: 'ape'
## The following object is masked from 'package:Biostrings':
## 
##     complement
dm_extremo_sul_msa_partial <- dist.ml(as.DNAbin(alignment_ba_1_to_350))

Plot distance matrix

Function table.paint() is from package adegenet. Load library adegenet:

library("adegenet")
## Warning: package 'adegenet' was built under R version 4.1.2
## Loading required package: ade4
## Warning: package 'ade4' was built under R version 4.1.2
## 
## Attaching package: 'ade4'
## The following object is masked from 'package:Biostrings':
## 
##     score
## The following object is masked from 'package:BiocGenerics':
## 
##     score
## 
##    /// adegenet 2.1.10 is loaded ////////////
## 
##    > overview: '?adegenet'
##    > tutorials/doc/questions: 'adegenetWeb()' 
##    > bug reports/feature requests: adegenetIssues()
## 
## Attaching package: 'adegenet'
## The following object is masked from 'package:phangorn':
## 
##     AICc
dm_extremo_sul_msa_partial_df <- as.data.frame(as.matrix(dm_extremo_sul_msa_partial))
table.paint(dm_extremo_sul_msa_partial_df, cleg=0, clabel.row=.5, clabel.col=.5)

Construct Phylogenetic Trees

Phylogenetic tree UPGMA method

treeUPGMA_extremo_sul_partial <- upgma(dm_extremo_sul_msa_partial_df)

Plot Phylogenetic Trees Extremo Sul

Plot UPGMA Extremo Sul

plot(treeUPGMA_extremo_sul_partial, main="UPGMA", col="red")

3) Visualize Distance Matrix and Phylogenetic Tree of Complete Genome

Coerce Biostring to DNA.bin

Read msa object that was exported

multiple_fasta_almt_ba_read <- readRDS("../dados/multiple_fasta_almt_ba.rds")

This is necessary so function dist.ml can take the DNA.bin object and process the Distance Matrix. Function dist.ml() is from package phangorn

library("phangorn")
dm_extremo_sul_msa_read <- dist.ml(as.DNAbin(multiple_fasta_almt_ba_read))

Plot distance matrix

Function table.paint() is from package adegenet. Load library adegenet:

library("adegenet")

dm_extremo_sul_msa_read_df <- as.data.frame(as.matrix(dm_extremo_sul_msa_read))
table.paint(dm_extremo_sul_msa_read_df, cleg=0, clabel.row=.5, clabel.col=.5)

Construct Phylogenetic Trees

Phylogenetic tree UPGMA method

treeUPGMA_extremo_sul <- upgma(dm_extremo_sul_msa_read_df)

Plot Phylogenetic Trees Extremo Sul

Plot UPGMA Extremo Sul

plot(treeUPGMA_extremo_sul, main="UPGMA", col="red")

4) Visualize the Spike Protein Region

Subset from positions 23000bp to 29903bp

These positions match approximately the region that encodes the Spike Protein sequence

seq_23000_to_29700 <- subseq(fastas_sars_cov2_ba, start = 23000, end = 29700)

Align sequences region spike

start_time <- Sys.time()
alignment_23000_to_29700 <- msa(seq_23000_to_29700)
## use default substitution matrix
end_time <- Sys.time()
end_time - start_time
## Time difference of 38.68454 secs
alignment_23000_to_29700
## CLUSTAL 2.1  
## 
## Call:
##    msa(seq_23000_to_29700)
## 
## MsaDNAMultipleAlignment with 10 rows and 6827 columns
##      aln                                                   names
##  [1] TGTAATGGTGTTGAAGGTTTTAATT...------------------------- NC_045512.2 Wuhan...
##  [2] ----------------GTTTTAATT...------------------------- hCoV-19/Brazil/ES...
##  [3] -------------------------...------------------------- hCoV-19/Brazil/BA...
##  [4] -------------------------...------------------------- hCoV-19/Brazil/BA...
##  [5] -------------------------...------------------------- hCoV-19/Brazil/BA...
##  [6] -------------------------...------------------------- hCoV-19/Brazil/BA...
##  [7] -------------------------...------------------------- hCoV-19/Brazil/BA...
##  [8] -------------------------...------------------------- hCoV-19/Brazil/MG...
##  [9] -------------------------...AGAGCCCTAATGTGTAAAATTAATT hCoV-19/bat/Yunna...
## [10] -------------------------...------------------------- hCoV-19/pangolin/...
##  Con -------------------------...------------------------- Consensus

Visualize Alignment Spike Protein

msaPrettyPrint(alignment_23000_to_29700, output="pdf",## y=c(164, 213),
               #subset=c(1:6), 
               showNames="none", showLogo="top",
               logoColors="rasmol", shadingMode="similar",
               showLegend=FALSE, askForOverwrite=FALSE)

Visualize the Spike Region Alignment

Subset the Spike Protein Region in original multi-fasta sequence

## Subset
seq_23000_to_23500 <- subseq(fastas_sars_cov2_ba, start = 23000, end = 23500)
## Align
alignment_23000_to_23500 <- msa(seq_23000_to_23500)
## use default substitution matrix

Visualize

msaPrettyPrint(alignment_23000_to_23500, output="pdf",## y=c(164, 213),
               #subset=c(1:6), 
               showNames="none", showLogo="top",
               logoColors="rasmol", shadingMode="similar",
               showLegend=FALSE, askForOverwrite=FALSE)

Save alignment as aligned fasta

writeXStringSet(as(unmasked(alignment_23000_to_23500), "XStringSet"), file="../dados/alignment_23000_to_23500.fasta")

Read file as aligned fasta

alignment_23000_to_23500_alnFasta <- readDNAStringSet(file="../dados/alignment_23000_to_23500.fasta")

View Spike Protein Region

  • Visualization of the Spike Protein Region alignment was made possible with library ggmsa and the work of Zhou (2022).

  • Load library.

SNP 23063 (N501Y)

  • Plot alignment at around position 23063bp, showing variant N501Y
ggmsa(alignment_23000_to_23500_alnFasta, 
      start = 40, end = 70, 
      char_width = 0.5, 
      seq_name = T) + geom_seqlogo() + geom_msaBar()
